-- place
(0, 'There''s usually one place from your past that still feels vivid when you close your eyes. Maybe it''s a room, a street corner, or somewhere outdoors. Think about what made that place feel like yours, and what you''d find if you went back today.', NULL, '{}', 'travel', 'place', '{}', 'favorite_place', '{travel,nostalgia}', 1),
(0, 'Picture the neighborhood where you were ten years old. Maybe it''s the sidewalk you rode your bike on, the yard where everyone gathered, or a shortcut only kids knew about. What did it look like, and who else was around?', NULL, '{}', 'childhood', 'place', '{}', 'childhood_place', '{childhood,neighborhood,home}', 2),
(0, 'Some places surprise you by feeling like home the second you walk in. Maybe it was a city you visited, a friend''s kitchen, or a spot you stumbled into by accident. Think about where that happened for you, and what it was about the place that clicked.', NULL, '{}', 'belonging', 'place', '{}', 'unexpected_home', '{belonging,travel}', 3),
(0, 'There''s probably a place you keep meaning to go back to but haven''t gotten around to yet. Maybe life got in the way, or maybe you''re a little afraid it won''t feel the same. What''s pulling you back, and what are you hoping to find?', NULL, '{}', 'travel', 'place', '{}', 'return_place', '{travel,longing}', 4),
(0, 'If you could walk through one building from your past, maybe a school, a grandparent''s house, or somewhere you worked, which would it be? Think about the hallways, the light, and what it felt like to move through that space.', NULL, '{}', 'nostalgia', 'place', '{}', 'building_memory', '{nostalgia,architecture}', 5),
(0, 'There''s probably a street or road you know so well you could navigate it with your eyes closed. Maybe you walked it every day, or drove it a thousand times. Think about what you passed along the way and who you were during that time.', NULL, '{}', 'familiarity', 'place', '{}', 'familiar_road', '{childhood,routine}', 6),
(0, 'Think about the last time you felt truly at peace somewhere. Maybe it was a porch, a beach, a particular chair, or just a quiet moment in your car. What was the setting, and what made it feel so still?', NULL, '{}', 'emotion', 'place', '{}', 'peaceful_place', '{peace,retreat}', 7),
(0, 'Some places don''t exist anymore, but you can still picture them perfectly. Maybe a store closed, a building was torn down, or a landscape changed. Think about one of those vanished places. What would someone miss if they never got to see it?', NULL, '{}', 'memory', 'place', '{}', 'vanished_place', '{nostalgia,loss}', 8),

-- feeling
(0, 'There''s usually a sound from childhood that can take you right back. Maybe it''s a screen door closing, a particular song playing in the kitchen, or someone calling your name from another room. What do you hear, and where does it put you?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{}', 'childhood_sound', '{childhood,sensory}', 9),
(0, 'Most people have a meal that carries a whole story with it. Maybe it''s something a grandparent made, a dish from a trip, or something you ate on an important night. Think about what you were eating, who was there, and what was going on in your life.', NULL, '{}', 'food', 'feeling', '{}', 'meaningful_meal', '{food,family,tradition}', 10),
(0, 'Certain smells can transport you in an instant. Maybe it''s fresh cut grass, a particular perfume, or something baking. Think about a scent that drops you into a specific moment. Where are you, and what''s happening around you?', NULL, '{}', 'sensory', 'feeling', '{}', 'smell_memory', '{sensory,nostalgia}', 11),
(0, 'Think about a time you felt deeply content doing something completely ordinary. Maybe you were cooking, reading, walking, or just sitting somewhere comfortable. What was the moment, and why did it feel like enough?', NULL, '{}', 'contentment', 'feeling', '{}', 'ordinary_joy', '{peace,simplicity}', 12),
(0, 'There''s probably something that makes you laugh every single time, no matter your mood. Maybe it''s a story someone tells, an inside joke, or a memory that catches you off guard. What is it, and who''s usually there when it happens?', NULL, '{}', 'humor', 'feeling', '{}', 'reliable_laugh', '{humor,joy}', 13),
(0, 'Songs have a way of locking in a whole era of your life. Think about one that takes you to a specific time. Maybe it played on the radio during a road trip, or you had it on repeat during a particular season. Where does the song put you?', NULL, '{}', 'music', 'feeling', '{}', 'song_memory', '{music,era,nostalgia}', 14),
(0, 'Kindness from a stranger can stay with you for years. Maybe someone helped you when you were lost, said something you needed to hear, or did a small thing that made a big difference. Think about who they were and what they did.', NULL, '{}', 'kindness', 'feeling', '{}', 'stranger_kindness', '{kindness,gratitude}', 15),
(0, 'There''s usually a feeling from childhood that you''d give anything to get back. Maybe it was the freedom of summer, the safety of being carried, or the excitement before a holiday. What was that feeling, and when did you last catch a glimpse of it?', NULL, '{}', 'childhood', 'feeling', '{}', 'childhood_feeling', '{childhood,innocence}', 16),

-- event
(0, 'Most people have at least one skill or piece of knowledge that surprises others. Maybe you can fix something unusual, cook something complicated, or do a thing nobody expects. Think about how you learned it and who, if anyone, taught you.', NULL, '{}', 'skills', 'event', '{}', 'unique_skill', '{skills,identity}', 17),
(0, 'Think about a moment you wish you''d captured in a photo but didn''t. Maybe things were moving too fast, or you were too caught up in the moment. What was happening, who was there, and what would the picture have shown?', NULL, '{}', 'regret', 'event', '{}', 'missed_photo', '{photography,moment}', 18),
(0, 'Some of the best days aren''t planned at all. Maybe you woke up with nothing to do and everything just fell into place. Think about a day like that. Who were you with, what unfolded, and why does it stand out?', NULL, '{}', 'spontaneity', 'event', '{}', 'unplanned_day', '{spontaneity,joy}', 19),
(0, 'Small decisions can end up steering your whole life in a new direction. Maybe you said yes to something on a whim, turned down a different road, or talked to someone you almost didn''t. Think about a tiny choice that turned out to be anything but.', NULL, '{}', 'decisions', 'event', '{}', 'small_decision', '{decisions,fate}', 20),
(0, 'Think about the hardest thing you''ve ever done that you''re genuinely glad you did. Maybe it was a move, a conversation, a commitment, or walking away from something. What made it so hard, and what came out of it?', NULL, '{}', 'resilience', 'event', '{}', 'hard_but_glad', '{resilience,growth}', 21),
(0, 'The best stories often come from trips that didn''t go as planned. Maybe the car broke down, the weather turned, or you ended up somewhere completely different. Think about an adventure that went sideways and became unforgettable.', NULL, '{}', 'adventure', 'event', '{}', 'misadventure', '{travel,humor,resilience}', 22),
(0, 'Think about the first big thing you did entirely on your own. Maybe it was moving somewhere new, making a decision nobody helped with, or handling something you weren''t sure you could. How did it go, and what did it teach you about yourself?', NULL, '{}', 'independence', 'event', '{}', 'first_solo', '{independence,growing_up}', 23),
(0, 'Some ordinary days stick in your memory with surprising detail. Not a birthday or holiday, just a regular day that you remember vividly. Maybe it was the weather, the company, or something subtle that happened. What was it about that day?', NULL, '{}', 'memory', 'event', '{}', 'vivid_ordinary', '{memory,detail}', 24),

-- people
(0, 'There''s usually someone who changed the direction of your life without even knowing it. Maybe they introduced you to something, said the right thing at the right time, or just modeled a different way of living. Who was that person, and what did they set in motion?', NULL, '{}', 'influence', 'people', '{}', 'unknown_influence', '{influence,gratitude}', 25),
(0, 'There''s usually one teacher, coach, or mentor who said something at exactly the right time. Think about who that was for you, what they said or did, and why it mattered so much.', NULL, '{}', 'mentors', 'people', '{}', 'life_teacher', '{mentors,lessons}', 26),
(0, 'Think about someone you haven''t talked to in years but still think about. Maybe it was a friend who moved away, a coworker from another life, or someone you just drifted from. What do you wonder about them, and what would you say if you could?', NULL, '{}', 'lost_touch', 'people', '{}', 'lost_touch', '{longing,friendship}', 27),
(0, 'Most families have a story that gets told over and over at gatherings. Think about yours. Who tells it best? Does the story change depending on who''s in the room? What''s the version only you know?', NULL, '{}', 'family', 'people', '{}', 'parent_wisdom', '{family,wisdom}', 28),
(0, 'Think about the funniest person you''ve ever known. Maybe they had perfect timing, a dry wit, or just a way of seeing the absurd in everything. What did they do that cracked you up, and what was it like to be around them?', NULL, '{}', 'humor', 'people', '{}', 'funniest_person', '{humor,friendship}', 29),
(0, 'Imagine introducing two people from completely different parts of your life who never met each other. Maybe a childhood friend and a coworker, or a grandparent and someone you met traveling. Who would you pick, and what do you think would happen?', NULL, '{}', 'relationships', 'people', '{}', 'crossover_intro', '{friendship,connections}', 30),
(0, 'Think about someone who believed in you before you believed in yourself. Maybe they saw something you couldn''t, pushed you toward something, or just refused to let you give up. Who were they, and how did their faith land on you?', NULL, '{}', 'support', 'people', '{}', 'early_believer', '{support,confidence}', 31),
(0, 'Good advice has a way of echoing in your head for years. Think about the best piece of advice anyone gave you. Maybe it came from a parent, a stranger, or a friend who knew you well. What was it, did you take it, and how did it play out?', NULL, '{}', 'wisdom', 'people', '{}', 'best_advice', '{wisdom,decisions}', 32),

-- object
(0, 'Most people have an object they''ve kept for years that others might toss without a second thought. Maybe it''s a ticket stub, a worn-out shirt, or something from a trip. Think about what you''ve held onto, and what it would tell someone about your life.', NULL, '{}', 'keepsakes', 'object', '{}', 'kept_object', '{keepsakes,sentiment}', 33),
(0, 'Think about something you own that tells a story no one would guess just by looking at it. Maybe it looks ordinary on a shelf but carries a whole chapter of your life. What is it, and what''s the story behind it?', NULL, '{}', 'possessions', 'object', '{}', 'story_object', '{possessions,stories}', 34),
(0, 'There''s usually a book, movie, or album that hit you in a way you didn''t expect. Maybe you picked it up casually and it rearranged something inside you. Think about what it was, when you found it, and what it stirred up.', NULL, '{}', 'culture', 'object', '{}', 'unexpected_media', '{culture,surprise}', 35),
(0, 'Check your wallet, bag, or pocket right now. Is there anything sentimental hiding in there? Maybe an old photo, a note someone wrote, or something you forgot you were carrying. What is it, and how did it end up traveling with you?', NULL, '{}', 'everyday', 'object', '{}', 'pocket_sentiment', '{everyday,sentiment}', 36),
(0, 'Think about something you made with your own hands that you''re still proud of. Maybe it was a piece of furniture, a meal for a crowd, a drawing, or something you fixed. What did you make, and what does it mean to you that you built it yourself?', NULL, '{}', 'creation', 'object', '{}', 'handmade_pride', '{creation,skills}', 37),
(0, 'Some gifts land harder than the giver probably realized. Maybe it was perfectly chosen, arrived at the right moment, or showed that someone understood you in a way you didn''t expect. Think about a gift like that. What was it, and who gave it to you?', NULL, '{}', 'gifts', 'object', '{}', 'meaningful_gift', '{gifts,gratitude}', 38),
(0, 'If your house were on fire and everyone was safe, what one thing would you grab on the way out? Maybe it''s irreplaceable, or maybe it just holds a feeling you can''t get anywhere else. What is it, and what would losing it mean?', NULL, '{}', 'priorities', 'object', '{}', 'fire_grab', '{priorities,sentiment}', 39),
(0, 'Clothing can hold memories the way a photograph does. Think about a jacket, a pair of shoes, or a favorite shirt that takes you back to a specific time. What were you wearing, and what was happening in your life when you wore it?', NULL, '{}', 'fashion', 'object', '{}', 'clothing_memory', '{fashion,era,nostalgia}', 40),

-- turning_point
(0, 'Some turning points don''t feel like turning points until years later. Maybe a conversation, a move, a chance encounter, or a quiet decision ended up changing everything. Think about one of those for you. When did you realize what it actually was?', NULL, '{}', 'reflection', 'turning_point', '{}', 'hidden_turning', '{reflection,hindsight}', 41),
(0, 'Think about something that used to terrify you but doesn''t anymore. Maybe it was public speaking, being alone, or something very specific. What changed? Was it a single moment, or did the fear fade slowly over time?', NULL, '{}', 'growth', 'turning_point', '{}', 'conquered_fear', '{growth,courage}', 42),
(0, 'There''s usually a moment when you first felt like an adult. Maybe it was a responsibility you didn''t ask for, a decision no one else could make, or just a quiet realization. How old were you, and what triggered it?', NULL, '{}', 'growing_up', 'turning_point', '{}', 'first_adult', '{growing_up,identity}', 43),
(0, 'Think about a belief you held strongly that you''ve completely reversed. Maybe it was about people, about how life works, or about yourself. What changed your mind? Was it a slow shift or one clear moment?', NULL, '{}', 'perspective', 'turning_point', '{}', 'changed_belief', '{perspective,growth}', 44),
(0, 'Some people know early what they want to do with their life, and some figure it out along the way, or stop needing a single answer. Think about where you fall. Was there a moment of clarity, or has it been more of an unfolding?', NULL, '{}', 'purpose', 'turning_point', '{}', 'life_direction', '{purpose,identity}', 45),
(0, 'Think about a goodbye that hit you harder than you expected. Maybe you didn''t realize how much that person, place, or chapter meant until it was ending. What was the goodbye, and what did it teach you about what you value?', NULL, '{}', 'loss', 'turning_point', '{}', 'hard_goodbye', '{loss,love}', 46),
(0, 'There''s usually a moment when you first realized your parents were just people figuring it out like everyone else. Maybe they made a mistake, showed vulnerability, or surprised you. When did that happen, and how did it change the way you saw them?', NULL, '{}', 'family', 'turning_point', '{}', 'parents_human', '{family,empathy,growing_up}', 47),
(0, 'Sometimes the best thing that ever happened to you started with something ending. A job, a friendship, a chapter you didn''t want to close. Think about a time when losing something turned out to be exactly what needed to happen. What ended, and what opened up?', NULL, '{}', 'endings', 'turning_point', '{}', 'necessary_ending', '{endings,growth,acceptance}', 48),
(0, 'Think about a risk you almost didn''t take. Maybe your stomach was in knots, people told you not to, or the timing felt wrong. What made you go through with it, and what happened on the other side?', NULL, '{}', 'courage', 'turning_point', '{}', 'worthy_risk', '{courage,decisions}', 49),
(0, 'Some moments split your life cleanly into before and after. Maybe it was a phone call, a diagnosis, a meeting, or a decision. Think about yours. What was on each side of that line, and how did you carry yourself through?', NULL, '{}', 'milestones', 'turning_point', '{}', 'before_after', '{milestones,transformation}', 50);


