-- anchor='person' (16 prompts)
(0, 'Think about a time {person_name} caught you completely off guard. Not a planned surprise, just something they said or did that you didn''t see coming. Maybe it was a kindness, a confession, or a side of them you hadn''t seen before. What happened?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'relationships', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_surprise', '{surprise,character}', 67),
(0, 'People teach us things without even trying. Think about something {person_name} taught you that they probably don''t know they taught. Maybe it was how they handled a hard moment, a habit you picked up, or a way of looking at things. What did you learn?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'lessons', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_lesson', '{lessons,influence}', 68),
(0, 'If {person_name} were describing you to a stranger, think about what they''d say first. Would it be something about your personality, a story they always tell, or something you do that they find funny or endearing? What do you think it would be?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'identity', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_describes_you', '{identity,perspective}', 69),
(0, 'Think about the funniest thing that ever happened between you and {person_name}. Maybe it was something that went wrong, a misunderstanding, or a moment that shouldn''t have been that funny but was. What happened, and does it still make you laugh?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'humor', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_funny', '{humor,bonding}', 70),
(0, 'Think about {person_name} and a moment between the two of you that wasn''t a big event. Maybe you were driving somewhere, sitting at a table, or doing something completely ordinary. What happened, and why does that moment still come back to you?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'moments', 'feeling', '{has_contacts}', 'person_small_moment', '{moments,significance}', 71),
(0, 'When you think about {person_name}, what''s the very first image that comes to mind? Maybe it''s their face in a certain light, a place you associate with them, or something they were doing. Don''t overthink it. What do you see?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'memory', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_first_memory', '{memory,association}', 72),
(0, 'Every person has something unmistakably theirs. Think about {person_name} and a phrase they always said, a gesture they made, or a habit that was so distinctly them nobody else could pull it off. What was it?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'character', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_signature', '{character,identity}', 73),
(0, 'Think about a meal, a trip, or a single day you shared with {person_name} that you''d relive if you could. Maybe it was a holiday, a random Tuesday, or an adventure that just happened. What made it so good, and what details do you remember?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'experiences', 'event', '{has_contacts}', 'person_relive', '{experiences,nostalgia}', 74),
(0, 'Think about the first time you met {person_name}. Maybe it was a quick introduction, a slow getting-to-know-you, or something more dramatic. Where were you, what were your first impressions, and did they turn out to be right?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'origins', 'event', '{has_contacts}', 'person_meeting', '{origins,beginnings}', 75),
(0, 'Every close relationship has a harmless disagreement that never gets resolved. Think about something you and {person_name} see completely differently but it doesn''t really matter. Maybe it''s a preference, a memory you remember differently, or a running debate.', 'person', '{person_name}', 'dynamics', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_disagree', '{dynamics,acceptance}', 76),
(0, 'Think about a hard time that {person_name} helped you get through. Maybe they showed up in a practical way, said the right thing, or just stayed nearby when everything felt unsteady. What did they do, and how did it feel to have them there?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'support', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_support', '{support,gratitude}', 77),
(0, 'There''s probably something you''d want {person_name} to know that you''ve never quite said. Maybe it''s a thank you, an apology, or just something about what they mean to you. If you could get the words right, what would you tell them?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'unsaid', 'feeling', '{has_contacts}', 'person_unsaid', '{unsaid,vulnerability}', 78),
(0, 'Think about a tradition or inside joke between you and {person_name}. Maybe it started by accident, maybe nobody else gets it, or maybe it''s become so routine you almost forgot how it began. What is it, and what keeps it going?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'bonding', 'event', '{has_contacts}', 'person_tradition', '{bonding,humor}', 79),
(0, 'Relationships change shape over the years. Think about how things between you and {person_name} have shifted. Maybe you''ve gotten closer, found a new rhythm, or grown in ways that surprised you both. What''s different now from how it started?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'evolution', 'turning_point', '{has_contacts}', 'person_evolution', '{evolution,growth}', 80),
(0, 'Think about a side of {person_name} that most people don''t get to see. Maybe they''re more tender than they seem, funnier in private, or carry something heavy that they keep to themselves. What do you know about them that others might miss?', 'person', '{person_name}', 'depth', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_hidden_side', '{depth,perception}', 81),
(0, 'If you had to capture {person_name} in one scene, not a description but a moment, what would it look like? Maybe they''re cooking, laughing, fixing something, or deep in thought. Put them somewhere real and let me see them the way you do.', 'person', '{person_name}', 'character', 'people', '{has_contacts}', 'person_scene', '{character,storytelling}', 82),

-- anchor='interest' (16 prompts)
(0, 'You mentioned {interest} is something you care about. Think about the very first time you got excited about it. Was there a person who introduced you, a moment that sparked it, or did it creep up on you slowly? What hooked you?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'identity', 'turning_point', '{has_interests}', 'interest_origin', '{identity,passion}', 83),
(0, 'There''s usually one person who''s most responsible for your connection to {interest}. Maybe they introduced you, challenged you, or just shared it with you in a way that made it stick. Who was that person, and what did they do?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'influence', 'people', '{has_interests}', 'interest_influencer', '{influence,gratitude}', 84),
(0, 'Think about a perfect day built around {interest}. Where would you be, who would be with you, and what would the day look like from start to finish? Don''t hold back. What would make it ideal?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'dreams', 'event', '{has_interests}', 'interest_perfect_day', '{dreams,joy}', 85),
(0, 'Most things that matter to people have a layer that outsiders don''t see. Think about {interest} and something about it that most people don''t fully appreciate or understand. What would you want them to know? What are they missing?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'passion', 'feeling', '{has_interests}', 'interest_misunderstood', '{passion,knowledge}', 86),
(0, 'Think about the best conversation you''ve ever had about {interest}. Maybe it was with someone who understood it deeply, or someone who asked the right questions. Who was it, what did you talk about, and why did it stand out?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'connection', 'people', '{has_interests}', 'interest_conversation', '{connection,ideas}', 87),
(0, 'There''s probably a memory tied to {interest} that still gives you a jolt of energy when you think about it. Maybe it was a breakthrough, a moment of pure joy, or a time when everything clicked. What happened, and where were you?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'energy', 'feeling', '{has_interests}', 'interest_energy', '{energy,passion}', 88),
(0, 'Shared passions have a way of connecting people who might never have met otherwise. Think about someone {interest} brought into your life. How did you meet, what did you bond over, and what would you have missed without them?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'connection', 'people', '{has_interests}', 'interest_connection', '{connection,serendipity}', 89),
(0, 'Think about the very first thing you ever made, did, or experienced in connection with {interest}. Maybe it was clumsy, thrilling, or laughably bad. What was that earliest moment like, and how does it compare to where you are with it now?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'beginnings', 'event', '{has_interests}', 'interest_first_time', '{beginnings,nostalgia}', 90),
(0, 'If you could share {interest} with one person from your past who never got to experience it with you, who would you pick? Maybe a grandparent, a friend, or someone who would have loved it. What would that look like?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'sharing', 'people', '{has_interests}', 'interest_share', '{sharing,connection}', 91),
(0, 'Think about a time {interest} got you through something difficult. Maybe it was a distraction, a comfort, or a way of processing what you were going through. What was happening in your life, and how did {interest} help?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'comfort', 'feeling', '{has_interests}', 'interest_comfort', '{comfort,coping}', 92),
(0, 'Nobody gets good at something without a few failures along the way. Think about a mistake or setback you had with {interest}. Maybe you messed something up, embarrassed yourself, or hit a wall. What happened, and what did it teach you?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'growth', 'event', '{has_interests}', 'interest_failure', '{growth,resilience}', 93),
(0, 'Think about where {interest} takes you, physically or mentally, that nothing else does. Maybe it puts you in a certain headspace, brings you to specific places, or gives you a kind of focus you can''t find elsewhere. What does it feel like when you''re deep in it?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'escape', 'place', '{has_interests}', 'interest_escape', '{escape,flow}', 94),
(0, 'Through {interest}, you''ve probably collected, built, or created something you''re proud of. Maybe it''s a skill you developed, a thing you made, or a collection that tells a story. What is it, and what does it represent about your journey?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'achievement', 'object', '{has_interests}', 'interest_creation', '{achievement,pride}', 95),
(0, 'Your relationship with {interest} has probably shifted over the years. Maybe it went from casual to serious, or changed in ways you didn''t expect. Think about how it''s evolved and what it means to you now compared to the beginning.', 'interest', '{interest}', 'evolution', 'turning_point', '{has_interests}', 'interest_evolution', '{evolution,depth}', 96),
(0, 'Sometimes our passions teach us things about ourselves we didn''t expect to learn. Think about the most surprising thing {interest} has revealed about who you are. Maybe it showed you a strength, a preference, or a side of yourself you didn''t know was there.', 'interest', '{interest}', 'self_discovery', 'feeling', '{has_interests}', 'interest_self', '{self_discovery,surprise}', 97),
(0, 'If a total beginner came to you wanting to fall in love with {interest}, where would you start them? Think about the entry point that would hook them. Would it be a place, a person, an experience, or something to watch, read, or try first?', 'interest', '{interest}', 'teaching', 'event', '{has_interests}', 'interest_intro', '{teaching,basics}', 98),

-- anchor='why_here' (16 prompts)
(0, 'You said you want to {why_text}. Think about the moment that made you decide now was the time. Maybe it was a conversation, a feeling that crept up, or something specific that happened. What tipped you over the edge?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'motivation', 'turning_point', '{has_why}', 'why_moment', '{motivation,decision}', 99),
(0, 'When you think about wanting to {why_text}, who''s the first person that comes to mind? Maybe it''s someone you want to do this for, someone who inspired it, or someone whose story you want to hold onto. Tell me about them.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'connections', 'people', '{has_why}', 'why_person', '{connections,legacy}', 100),
(0, 'Imagine you actually accomplish {why_text}. Think about what that would feel like. Not just the outcome, but the moment you realize it''s done. Who''s with you? What changes? What can you finally let go of?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'meaning', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_meaning', '{meaning,purpose}', 101),
(0, 'If you had to start with just one story as part of {why_text}, which would it be? Maybe it''s the most important one, the one that''s hardest to tell, or the one that captures something essential. What story is at the top of the list?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'priorities', 'event', '{has_why}', 'why_first_story', '{priorities,storytelling}', 102),
(0, 'Think about who you hope will eventually see or benefit from {why_text}. Maybe it''s a specific person, a future generation, or even yourself. What do you hope they feel when they encounter what you''ve created?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'legacy', 'people', '{has_why}', 'why_audience', '{legacy,family}', 103),
(0, 'Was there someone who planted the seed for {why_text}? Maybe they did something similar, said something that stuck, or just lived in a way that made you want to try. Think about who that was and what they sparked in you.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'inspiration', 'people', '{has_why}', 'why_inspiration', '{inspiration,role_models}', 104),
(0, 'Think about a specific memory that perfectly captures why {why_text} matters to you. Not a reason, a moment. Maybe it was something someone said, a feeling you had, or a scene that keeps coming back. What was it?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'core_memory', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_core_memory', '{core_memory,purpose}', 105),
(0, 'Starting something meaningful usually comes with surprises. Think about the hardest part of {why_text} that you didn''t see coming. Maybe it''s emotional, logistical, or something about yourself that surfaced. What caught you off guard?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'challenges', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_challenge', '{challenges,honesty}', 106),
(0, 'If you could only {why_text} for one person, who would it be? Think about why they come to mind first. Maybe it''s because of what they''ve given you, what they need to hear, or what you''d want them to carry with them.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'dedication', 'people', '{has_why}', 'why_one_person', '{dedication,love}', 107),
(0, 'Think about which part of your past feels most important to include as you {why_text}. Maybe it''s a specific era, a relationship, or a series of moments that shaped who you became. What can''t be left out?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'curation', 'event', '{has_why}', 'why_important_past', '{curation,reflection}', 108),
(0, 'Is there a part of {why_text} that makes you nervous? Maybe you''re worried about getting it wrong, leaving something out, or sharing something that feels too raw. Think about what feels vulnerable about this, and why it matters anyway.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'vulnerability', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_fear', '{vulnerability,perfectionism}', 109),
(0, 'Think about the moment when {why_text} is actually finished. Picture it clearly. Where are you, how does your body feel, and what''s the first thing you want to do? Is it relief, pride, or something more complicated?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'completion', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_completion', '{completion,relief}', 110),
(0, 'Has anything happened recently that reminded you why you want to {why_text}? Maybe a conversation, a moment with someone, or just a quiet thought that brought it all back. What was it, and what did it stir up?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'reinforcement', 'event', '{has_why}', 'why_conversation', '{reinforcement,connection}', 111),
(0, 'Think about when you first realized you wanted to {why_text}. Was it a sudden realization or something that built slowly? Maybe it started as a vague feeling and sharpened over time. Walk me through how you got to the decision.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'origins', 'turning_point', '{has_why}', 'why_realization', '{origins,awareness}', 112),
(0, 'There''s probably a detail about your life that most people don''t know, but it matters deeply for {why_text}. Maybe it''s a private experience, a quiet truth, or something you''ve carried without sharing. What is it, and why does it belong in this story?', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'hidden', 'feeling', '{has_why}', 'why_hidden_detail', '{hidden,authenticity}', 113),
(0, 'If {why_text} could change just one thing for someone you love, what would you want that to be? Maybe it''s understanding, connection, or a feeling of being known. Think about the specific difference you hope it makes.', 'why_here', '{why_text}', 'impact', 'people', '{has_why}', 'why_impact', '{impact,hope}', 114),

-- anchor='era' (16 prompts)
(0, 'Think about something you believed at twenty that you''ve completely changed your mind about. Maybe it was about love, work, people, or yourself. What did you used to think, what do you think now, and what changed you?', 'era', '{}', 'perspective', 'turning_point', '{has_era}', 'era_belief_change', '{perspective,growth}', 115),
(0, 'Your {decade}s probably taught you something nobody could have told you in advance. Think about a lesson from that time that you wish someone had whispered to you earlier. What was it, and how did you end up learning it the hard way?', 'era', '{decade}', 'wisdom', 'feeling', '{has_era}', 'era_lesson', '{wisdom,hindsight}', 116),
(0, 'Think about something you were completely obsessed with in your {decade}s that you''d almost forgotten about until right now. Maybe it was a hobby, a show, a person, or a goal. What was it, and what would your past self think of you moving on from it?', 'era', '{decade}', 'nostalgia', 'object', '{has_era}', 'era_obsession', '{nostalgia,passions}', 117),
(0, 'There''s usually a friendship from a specific era that shaped who you became. Think about someone from your {decade}s who influenced you deeply. Maybe you''re still close, or maybe you drifted. What did that friendship give you?', 'era', '{decade}', 'friendship', 'people', '{has_era}', 'era_friendship', '{friendship,influence}', 118),
(0, 'Think about what you looked like in your {decade}s, how you dressed, how you carried yourself. How did you feel about your appearance then? Is there a gap between how you saw yourself and how you''d see those photos now?', 'era', '{decade}', 'self_image', 'feeling', '{has_era}', 'era_appearance', '{self_image,identity}', 119),
(0, 'Walk me through a typical day in your {decade}s. What time did you wake up, where did you go, who did you see, and what did the rhythm of your life feel like? Think about the small details, not just the big events.', 'era', '{decade}', 'routine', 'event', '{has_era}', 'era_routine', '{routine,lifestyle}', 120),
(0, 'Think about a risk you took in your {decade}s that still surprises you. Maybe it was a move, a relationship, a career change, or just saying something bold. What made you go for it, and how do you feel about it now?', 'era', '{decade}', 'courage', 'event', '{has_era}', 'era_risk', '{courage,surprise}', 121),
(0, 'Music and memory are tightly linked. Think about the soundtrack of your {decade}s. What was playing, and what were you doing while it played? Maybe it was in your car, at a party, or on repeat in your room. Where does the music take you?', 'era', '{decade}', 'music', 'feeling', '{has_era}', 'era_music', '{music,atmosphere}', 122),
(0, 'Think about who you were trying to become in your {decade}s. Maybe you had a clear picture, or maybe you were just reaching for something you couldn''t name. What were you chasing, and how close did you get?', 'era', '{decade}', 'ambition', 'turning_point', '{has_era}', 'era_ambition', '{ambition,identity}', 123),
(0, 'Think about the funniest thing that happened to you in your {decade}s. Maybe it was embarrassing at the time, or maybe everyone was laughing. What was the situation, who was there, and does the story get better every time you tell it?', 'era', '{decade}', 'humor', 'event', '{has_era}', 'era_funny', '{humor,stories}', 124),
(0, 'Love shows up differently at different ages. Think about what love looked like in your {decade}s. Maybe it was passionate, quiet, complicated, or brand new. Who was at the center of it, and what did you learn about love during that time?', 'era', '{decade}', 'love', 'feeling', '{has_era}', 'era_love', '{love,romance}', 125),
(0, 'Fear changes as we do. Think about what you were most afraid of in your {decade}s. Maybe it was failure, loneliness, something happening to someone you love, or something very specific. Does it still scare you, or has a new fear taken its place?', 'era', '{decade}', 'fears', 'feeling', '{has_era}', 'era_fear', '{fears,growth}', 126),
(0, 'Some places define an era. Think about a place that belongs to your {decade}s more than any other. Maybe it''s where you lived, where you hung out, or where important things happened. What was it, and what does it represent about that time?', 'era', '{decade}', 'places', 'place', '{has_era}', 'era_place', '{places,era}', 127),
(0, 'Think about a job or role you held in your {decade}s that taught you something unexpected. Maybe the work itself wasn''t memorable, but the people, the lessons, or the way it changed you stuck around. What did you take from it?', 'era', '{decade}', 'work', 'event', '{has_era}', 'era_job', '{work,lessons}', 128),
(0, 'If you could go back and do one thing differently in your {decade}s, what would it be? Maybe it''s a conversation you''d have, a chance you''d take, or a boundary you''d set. What would change, and what do you think the ripple effect would be?', 'era', '{decade}', 'regret', 'turning_point', '{has_era}', 'era_redo', '{regret,wisdom}', 129),
